          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". After irradiation of the silicon samples, the",
                "contents of Na-24 are measured.",
                " Na-24 can be produced either by impurities, i.e.:",
                "         Na-23(n,g) (with thermal neutrons), or",
                "         Al-27(n,a) (with fast neutrons)",
                " or by the reaction",
                "         Si-28(n,ap), which has a q-value of 14.7 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".60 cm3."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cd-wrapped Si irradiated in the reactor core gave",
                "higher amounts of Na-24 than Si irradiated in the 14MeV",
                "neutron generator. Because of the high q-value, it was",
                "assumed that the Si-28(n,ap)reaction could not take",
                "place in the 14MeV neutron beam. Therefore, the",
                "difference of Na-24 produced in the fission spectrum of",
                "the reactor and in the 14MeV beam was attributed to the",
                "Si-28(n,ap) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For the Na-23(n,g) reaction with fast neutrons"
              ]
            }
          ],
